         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/4/87. ¶  ¶ Herewith, honored and dear Sir, I beg to send you manuscripts and specimens of two plants, new to your territory, trusting that the notes will prove acceptable to the L.S. ¶  of N.S.W. P...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.04.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William John Macleay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS 9877, Linnean Society of NSW papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/4/87.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith, honored and dear Sir, I beg to send you manuscripts and specimens of two plants, new to your territory, trusting that the notes will prove acceptable to the L.S.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Linnean Society.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> of N.S.W. Perhaps you will allow me a look on the proof, before it is printed off.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, that the L.S. of N.S.W. will join with the R.S. &amp; RGS.,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Society of NSW, Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (NSW Branch).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> to recommend some support from your Government for the forthcoming contemplated antarctic expedition. The Premier of Victoria and his hon. Colleagues in the Ministry here view with favor the proposition, and would probably sanction a grant for the purpose, if the other colonies would also support the intended enterprise to some extent.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Midsummer would be the best time for the exploration of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Mt. Seaview</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> It would not cost much to cut a mere track for pedestrians to the summit, as some of the settlements are not far from the mount. It seems extraordinary, that fully a century should have elapsed, ere this high Mt, (and yet comparatively so near the metropolis of N.S.W.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Sydney.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>) became scaled. It must be also of entomol. interest, and may offer a new gold-field for the colony there.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
